    <item>
      <title>Proxmox Email Alerts Setup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/proxmox-email-alerts-setup/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 04 Jun 2024 13:09:00 +1000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/proxmox-email-alerts-setup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-install-mailutils&#34;&gt;1. Install mailutils&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;SSH into proxmox node and become root user. Run the following commands to download extra software dependencies we&amp;rsquo;ll need.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;apt update&#xA;apt install -y libsasl2-modules mailutils&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-enable-2fa-for-the-gmail-account&#34;&gt;2. Enable 2FA for the gmail account.&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is the account that will be used by proxmox to send emails. Go to &lt;a href=&#34;https://myaccount.google.com/security&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;security settings&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;3-create-app-password-for-the-account&#34;&gt;3. Create app password for the account.&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;a href=&#34;https://security.google.com/settings/security/apppasswords&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;App Passwords&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select app: &lt;code&gt;Mail&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select device: &lt;code&gt;Other&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Type in: &lt;code&gt;Proxmox&lt;/code&gt; or whatever you want here&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;4-setup-gmail-credentials&#34;&gt;4. Setup gmail credentials&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Write gmail credentials to file and hash it. Again, make sure you are root.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Securing Your Nas Against Ransomware</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/securing-your-nas---with-nutshell/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 May 2024 10:39:36 +1000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/securing-your-nas---with-nutshell/</guid>
      <description>&lt;script src=&#34;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/ncase/nutshell/nutshell.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;threat&#34;&gt;Threat&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m on a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.reddit.com/r/synology/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;synology sub-reddit&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA; page and I see posts like this every couple of months and it terrifies me:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/securing-your-nas---with-nutshell/attack.png&#34; width=&#34;1000&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is an example of Ransomware.&#xA;Ransomware is a type of malicious software designed to block access to a computer system or files until a sum of money, or &amp;ldquo;ransom,&amp;rdquo; is paid. It typically works by encrypting the victim&amp;rsquo;s files or locking them behind a password, rendering them inaccessible. Once the ransomware is activated, the victim is presented with instructions on how to pay the ransom, often in cryptocurrency, in exchange for a decryption key or password. Ransomware attacks can be devastating for individuals and organizations, causing data loss, financial harm, and disrupting normal operations. Cybersecurity experts recommend regularly backing up data, maintaining updated software, and exercising caution when clicking on links or downloading files to prevent falling victim to ransomware attacks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
